  "text": "The JCE provider architecture centers on Cipher.getInstance() (Cipher.java), which resolves a cryptographic service by querying the Security class. Security (Security.java) manages the list of registered security providers, reading the default provider order from the java.security configuration file (src/java.base/share/conf/security/java.security). The abstract Provider class (Provider.java) defines the base for all security providers and contains the inner Service class that maps algorithm names to implementation classes. SunJCE (SunJCE.java) is the default JCE provider that extends Provider and registers cipher implementations (RSA, DES, AES, Blowfish, ChaCha20, etc.) via its putEntries() method. The provider order in java.security determines which implementation is selected when multiple providers offer the same algorithm.",
